    pl "You do tend to talk much louder and faster during our morning assemblies and in the chapel."


translate English day3_hk_T_47825b92:


    hk "Well, of course. I'm preaching the good gospel...!"


translate English day3_hk_T_2e9cd717:


    hk "As your teacher, it would be unbecoming for me to not know what I'm talking about."


translate English day3_hk_T_eb0aabc0:


    hk "Those are all very different situations. To be frank, I'm not the best when it comes to expressing my personal opinions."


translate English day3_hk_T_6189f0a7:


    pl "By the way, what's the silver rosary in the temple used for?"


translate English day3_hk_T_64f8e60f:


    hk "It's a kind of identifier that marks the temple priests."


translate English day3_hk_T_c45a4986:


    hk "Since each is inscribed with the name of the priest it belongs to,"


translate English day3_hk_T_3001f43b:


    hk "it takes about a week to replace them if lost or damaged."


translate English day3_hk_T_ae20081b:


    pl "So, what do you think we'll have for lunch tomorrow?"


translate English day3_hk_T_72546cbe:


    hk "Hrmmmm..."


translate English day3_hk_T_4d6586b3:


    hk "...Gratin, perhaps?"


translate English day3_hk_T_617a4c70:


    pl "Ooh, interesting. I found an unexpected weakness."


translate English day3_hk_T_47fb118e:


    hk "Ugh! Don't mock your elders, child!" with sshake


translate English day3_hk_T_d3d90bfb:


    nar "I wonder if she uses such vague, flowery language in order to hide how bad she is at expressing herself?"


translate English day3_hk_T_557f9d0c:


    nar "As someone who's quick to put my thoughts into words, it's hard for me to understand."


translate English day3_hk_T_4f1ddefe:


    nar "The more transparent someone appears, the more suspicious I get. Though this time it's less about her as a person and more about her role as a bishop."


translate English day3_hk_T_c7872cee:


    pl "The priests in the temple are so unfeeling that it's clear they don't even care about you."


translate English day3_hk_T_3ed282b9:


    hk "Perhaps it never bothered me in the same way because I never viewed it as problematic."


translate English day3_hk_T_eca10bbc:


    hk "I guess I've never been bitter about the various obstacles thrown in my way as I meander through life."


translate English day3_hk_T_63b08ba5:


    pl "Even if people accuse you of things behind your back or speak bad about you?"


translate English day3_hk_T_b9255895:


    hk "Mm. I'm still not bitter."


translate English day3_hk_T_44776a99:


    hk "Negative feelings only give birth to more negativity. Everything revolves around Divine Providence."


translate English day3_hk_T_e38f6984:


    hk "The Cleanup Department exists to help keep the capital and the temple running. "


translate English day3_hk_T_db9b76c5:


    hk "When that hatred and rage is passed on to me, then it's just more marvelous proof that the Cleanup Department is working as intended."


translate English day3_hk_T_1e8cb570:


    pl "Uh-huh... So everything really is for the sake of the nation?"


translate English day3_hk_T_9d400539:


    hk "But of course. The Cleanup Department was created for the sake of the people. "


translate English day3_hk_T_c4b51fdb:


    hk "Besides, there's no way I could feel bitter resentment or being graced with this role from our blessed father above."


translate English day3_hk_T_667af81b:


    pl "If you're okay with it then I guess that's fine, but I'm not sure if the other priests, including myself, see it that way..."


translate English day3_hk_T_e6bc1b82:


    hk "And yet the Cleanup Department seems to be thriving, with all the priests carrying out their respective roles marvelously...!"


translate English day3_hk_T_fb0ada11:


    hk "And how grateful I am because of it "


translate English day3_hk_T_05f2036f:


    nar "I can feel my heart sinking again. I don't think she has any idea the kind of lives the folks under her care are leading. "


translate English day3_hk_T_9e8b9580:


    nar "She seems to think the priests would talk to her if there was a problem, but I strongly disagree."


translate English day3_hk_T_db1bc92e:


    nar "She must know that if she's a bishop."


translate English day3_hk_T_bc4bbf1e:


    pl "Are you aware that the priests in the Cleanup Department don't get along?"


translate English day3_hk_T_04822b52:


    hk "...They don't?"


translate English day3_hk_T_2aee79a7:


    pl "Earlier today, I saw a fight suddenly break out in the middle of a cleanup job. "


translate English day3_hk_T_d1bc47b5:


    pl "One guy was beat up so bad, his face was a bloody mess. "


translate English day3_hk_T_88f89c4e:


    pl "It wasn't an isolated incident either. Bullying runs rampant and gossip flows freely..."


translate English day3_hk_T_a0868a5e:


    hk "That simply can't be...!"


translate English day3_hk_T_6edff510:


    pl "Granted, I might have just happened to run into a couple bad faith actors, but..."


translate English day3_hk_T_ba6cc64d:


    pl "Well, the number of incidents seems fairly high when you consider I've only been here for less than three days."


translate English day3_hk_T_f48d79bd:


    nar "A shadow falls over her face. I shut my mouth perhaps a moment too late, though I don't think anything I said was uncalled for."


translate English day3_hk_T_751e7029:


    nar "I wanted to be sure. I'd heard enough rumors about the bishop, such as how incompetent she is and how fully dependent on her family's good name."


translate English day3_hk_T_1fffeda1:


    nar "I've always wondered how much truth lays in malicious gossip."


translate English day3_hk_T_48098bfc:


    nar "But she merely looks up at me again, her usual smile still on her face."


translate English day3_hk_T_46699a06:


    hk "Brother [na], I am not indifferent to the things that happen here."


translate English day3_hk_T_0e98f524:


    nar "Her voice is as light and calm as always, though there's an unusual resolute tone to it."


translate English day3_hk_T_2bb9d622:


    hk "I know what happens in my department."


translate English day3_hk_T_5a03436a:


    pl "Huh? Then why don't you do anything about it? If you said something about it, then the priests would have to listen to you, right?"


translate English day3_hk_T_d52f03c1:


    hk "I'm pretty sure I've already told you plenty of times before that I have no intention of getting involved more than I already have."


translate English day3_hk_T_ab91dbbe:


    hk "I've talked to them, face to face, warning them about their behavior..."


translate English day3_hk_T_51a367b5:


    pl "If nothing changes, then maybe more draconian measures are necessary."


translate English day3_hk_T_ec311602:


    hk "I disagree. I believe in the priests who work here. "


translate English day3_hk_T_73891100:


    hk "As I mentioned earlier, negative feelings only give birth to more negativity. "


translate English day3_hk_T_5f24319f:


    hk "I have no intention of purposefully abandoning the priests in my care."


translate English day3_hk_T_aa9f1059:


    pl "Folks here call your approach simplistic and irresponsible... Who's going to take you seriously when you place all your faith in one magical being?"


translate English day3_hk_T_7f32d663:


    hk "Brother [na], there is no guarantee that he who I place my faith in will ever respond. "


translate English day3_hk_T_342edef3:


    hk "And yet my faith never wavers. I trust him, wholly and truly. I've never once lost sight of him."


translate English day3_hk_T_976994d5:


    nar "I didn't understand what she meant at first, but after talking with Haku, I understand her reasoning a lot better."


translate English day3_hk_T_b9fca7cb:


    nar "Getting involved with the infighting only puts a bandaid on the situation without leading to a lasting solution."


translate English day3_hk_T_608fc072:


    nar "Folks don't make peace over a forced handshake. It is impossible to pray away the hatred harbored in someone else's heart. "


translate English day3_hk_T_e6a1ae33:


    nar "That's probably what she's trying to say."


translate English day3_hk_T_860973d4:


    pl "What if I end up being transferred to a different department?"


translate English day3_hk_T_fe7b7861:


    hk "Heh!"


translate English day3_hk_T_848d3ed9:


    nar "Her hair sways lightly with the excessively tall woman's back and forth movements. Her hair seems to express her sentiments before she speaks them, like an animal's twitching tail."


translate English day3_hk_T_d86fc85d:


    hk "My department is different than the others."


translate English day3_hk_T_5cfd45f7:


    hk "The other departments are filled with folks who chose to be there. The Cleanup Department, meanwhile, is where those who've been pushed to the limits of reality end up."


translate English day3_hk_T_259eb0dd:


    pl "The way you describe it makes it sound like..."


translate English day3_hk_T_a1542e07:


    hk "Hell itself?"


translate English day3_hk_T_bbd23797:


    nar "The word--Hell--had faintly flitted through my mind, only to come out her mouth."


translate English day3_hk_T_0298e378:


    nar "I'm too stunned to nod, let alone answer, but my reaction clearly confirms her question."


translate English day3_hk_T_537619a8:


    nar "Seeing my reaction, she brings her sleeve up to cover her smile."


translate English day3_hk_T_ca679393:


    hk "And yet, this department ISN'T hell. As living creatures, all those who have fallen here can still rise above it. "


translate English day3_hk_T_ac98ebb0:


    hk "Which is partly why I'm charged with teaching the priests in my care. So that you may face your own sins and learn to love one another "


translate English day3_hk_T_6f11c82b:


    pl "Have you ever considered that your way of thinking might be wrong?"


translate English day3_hk_T_cd0b306d:


    hk "Not at all. I believe in my teachings and in the wisdom bestowed upon me by God, our father who art in heaven."


translate English day3_hk_T_63cfacba:


    hk "If you cannot believe in yourself, then how do you expect others to do so?"


translate English day3_hk_T_4dc39e6e:


    pl "The other priests don't seem to like you that much."


translate English day3_hk_T_31f179ae:


    hk "And yet I continue to love them all equally."


translate English day3_hk_T_e1ff3c75:


    pl "Ugh... This is exactly what I mean."


translate English day3_hk_T_e1a578c1:


    hk "That's what I refer to as \"belief.\""


translate English day3_hk_T_b6941571:


    nar "The rising smoke slowly begins dissipating. I cough soundlessly, my lungs and throat irritated by the haze."


translate English day3_hk_T_7ac79219:


    nar "I still don't understand her."


translate English day3_hk_T_09f9f75b:


    nar "I can usually figure out what someone's thinking or what exactly they want after talking to them, "


translate English day3_hk_T_a133e036:


    nar "but being unable to get a good read on the bishop means I have no idea how to deal with her."


translate English day3_hk_T_b8393d83:


    nar "The more information I glean from her, the more lost I feel. Staring fixedly at her, she always seems to look away the moment our eyes meet."


translate English day3_hk_T_8b7fe955:


    nar "Perhaps the only thing I've learned is that anything I say to her is useless. "


translate English day3_hk_T_61277cc5:


    nar "That she's not interested in figuring out a direct solution because she's living in an entirely different reality."


translate English day3_hk_T_cf51e2a3:


    nar "But that's not necessarily so bad. Thanks to that, I don't have to consider my words quite as carefully as I do when speaking to others."


translate English day3_hk_T_ea7b2835:


    pl "Actually, a bunch of stuff happened in town today."


translate English day3_hk_T_02280d9f:


    hk "A bunch of stuff? Such as...?"


translate English day3_hk_T_1b0f625d:


    pl "I wasn't seriously injured, but a bunch of folks expressed their frustration and anger toward me. "


translate English day3_hk_T_49f6c356:


    pl "I'd never met them before, and I have no idea what they've been through..."


translate English day3_hk_T_e0ed5628:


    hk "It happens."


translate English day3_hk_T_84a07064:


    pl "I felt a lot of ways about what happened."


translate English day3_hk_T_9dcac77b:


    pl "Like if I'm going to have to endure this much abuse, I'm not sure if I'm really qualified for the job..."


translate English day3_hk_T_2ba7fd0e:


    hk "They are, of course, children of God, but we, too, despite being the recipients of their negativity, are *also* children of God. A person only becomes a person with the acquisition of emotions."


translate English day3_hk_T_2e9fb9bd:


    nar "She steps closer to me before placing her hand on my shoulder. Though surprised at first, I soon calm down."


translate English day3_hk_T_68e67248:


    nar "Her hand, covered in hard leather, holds no trace of warmth or comfort, yet it grounded me."


translate English day3_hk_T_d5162f5f:


    nar "She squeezes my shoulder gently, as if trying to alleviate my concern."


translate English day3_hk_T_c87743fd:


    hk "Sadness is sadness, pain is pain, regret is regret... All of those feelings are valid."


translate English day3_hk_T_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "..."


translate English day3_hk_T_85595dba:


    hk "Keep doing your best, Brother..."


translate English day3_hk_T_764a97b2:


    pl "Right... I was honestly surprised at first. I chalked it up to personal reasons or my role in the department."


translate English day3_hk_T_d5500f1b:


    hk "Right, exactly. Honesty is the best policy!"


translate English day3_hk_T_09c9a705:


    pl "I'm sure you're busy every day putting out multitudes of fires..."


translate English day3_hk_T_57479c82:


    hk "Oh, but I looove helping people out!"


translate English day3_hk_T_28b59507:


    pl "That's not exactly what I meant..."


translate English day3_hk_T_d596c7b9:


    hk "That I'm busy helping make sure this place runs smoothly means you must feel my presence everywhere you go, right?"


translate English day3_hk_T_d1ff4a7c:


    pl "The way you describe it makes you sound like a workaholic... It depends on the job, right? "


translate English day3_hk_T_8d44e112:


    pl "If you want to be appreciated so much, why not work in a job that only you can do?"


translate English day3_hk_T_26ee5bf1:


    hk "I strongly believe this job is something only I can do this well."


translate English day3_hk_T_fc8b0c5e:


    pl "What... running around like a chicken with their head cut off?"


translate English day3_hk_T_1be948f6:


    hk "Listening to your problems and your fellow priests."


translate English day3_hk_T_b76592a7:


    pl "Listening to our problems, huh?"


translate English day3_hk_T_caa611bc:


    hk "The Cleanup Department exists for the people, but the bishop exists for the priests. "


translate English day3_hk_T_e0a40994:


    hk "You may leave us one day for the Magic Department, Brother [na], but for now, "


translate English day3_hk_T_f4492372:


    hk "you're one of us. "


translate English day3_hk_T_20ba2de3:


    hk "And it's my duty as your bishop to assist you."


translate English day3_hk_T_c7a9916c:


    hk "So I urge you to come to me with any hardships or problems you might face."


translate English day3_hk_T_eb1e660c_2:


    pl "......"


translate English day3_hk_T_4d7227cf:


    nar "There's a pause in our conversation. I glance at her before stepping away. "


translate English day3_hk_T_0ceafa6a:


    nar "The shoulder her hand rested on a moment ago feels heavier than the other. I shake my head once before answering."


translate English day3_hk_T_959d4f02:


    pl "I appreciate it, but I'm fine. There's nothing weighing on me..."


translate English day3_hk_T_0da831c5:


    nar "I have no intention of telling her what I'm going through. "


translate English day3_hk_T_4b638192:


    nar "I have a hard enough confiding in other people, and I have no doubt nothing good will come from her knowing. "


translate English day3_hk_T_a46ca578:


    nar "She is, in fact, the last person I'd ever tell my secrets to."


translate English day3_hk_T_d5667605:


    nar "This feeling of rejection probably stems from my inability to trust her."


translate English day3_hk_T_cdbc3c5d:


    hk "I see. Well, if there's anything else you wish to share with me, I'm all ears. "


translate English day3_hk_T_14f9134a:


    hk "I looooove listening to stories!"


translate English day3_hk_T_22b19d18:


    pl "But you're always so busy."


translate English day3_hk_T_5e210200:


    nar "I still have no idea how trustworthy she is. "


translate English day3_hk_T_4600c438:


    nar "One's ability can't be gleaned from appearances alone, and I don't know the first thing about the type of person she truly is."


translate English day3_hk_T_bdd346b0:


    nar "I seem to be subconsciously wary of her."


translate English day3_hk_T_37612989:


    nar "Though now I understand how she became the bishop of the Cleanup Department."


translate English day3_hk_T_ba0a40f9:


    hk "Do you enjoy living here, [na]? Have you grown to appeciate the temple?"


translate English day3_hk_T_02655cc7:


    nar "It feels like a giant cage to me, designed to keep goats, rabbits, and all manner of animals trapped inside. "


translate English day3_hk_T_64dfef13:


    nar "All guarded by a bishop who refuses to get involved with any of their affairs unless it involves a rampaging beast attempting to escape. That's how she keeps the peace here."


translate English day3_hk_T_559dbed2:


    pl "Anyone who says they like it here has clearly lost their damn mind."


translate English day3_hk_T_d2ca19e7:


    nar "I tried to give her the answer she wants to hear, but can't bring myself to do so. She merely laughs in response before walking away."


translate English day3_hk_T_acc474ff:


    nar "Unable to ask her directly what kind of person she is, I'm left feeling a mix of emotions. I don't hate her, but I do hate the department itself."


translate English day3_hk_T_2734c6dd:


    nar "The Cleanup Department in particular seems especially barbaric."


translate English day3_hk_F_cd71af33:


    "\n The dormitory is crowded, as usual, but as soon as I put some distance between us, the crowds around me instantly vanish. "


translate English day3_hk_F_5f7deeb9:


    "I'm on the path leading toward the workplace. It's wide enough for several people to walk side by side, and yet it's late enough that there's no one here but me. Just like yesterday."


translate English day3_hk_F_ca5858f4:


    "Smoke rises up into the black sky above, the acrid air irritating my lungs and making me cough. The outdoors workplace feels cooler but is far from clean thanks to the proliferation of soot."


translate English day3_hk_F_ad942e0f:


    et "Speaking of air quality, the town from earlier today wasn't that clean, either. The heavy pollution in the capital is, indeed, a big problem. And this is where we deal with the corpses we find, surrounded by smoke. Well, actually, there's only one person who deals with them."


translate English day3_hk_F_0cf95171:



    nvl clear
    "\n Within the cramped room, the scorched floor--splattered with the dried up remains of yellow soup--lies an old man's corpse on the verge of becoming a Lost Soul."


translate English day3_hk_F_1b2d9c5f:


    "Disposal takes almost no time at all, though, so there's no danger. The only movement to be found being is his blackened limbs. His skinny arms and legs, nothing more than skin and bone, twitch and jerk as if there's still life in him, which is when the other guy brings his sword down. I simply stand there, watching from afar."


translate English day3_hk_F_326d6e6e:


    et "Memories of what I've seen leave me feeling excessively uncomfortable. Is whatever's burning in the incinerator part of a dead body? I find it harder to breathe the closer I get. Peering in the incinerator, there's nothing left but charred ash, burned far beyond recognition..."


translate English day3_hk_F_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day3_gr_4d533762:


    nar "I race to the infirmary, a place I've become very familiar with."


translate English day3_gr_93092762:


    nar "As soon as I catch sight of the door, always left open in a welcoming gesture to the priests here, my frozen body is immediately enveloped in warmth and I catch the faint whiff of cinnamon."


translate English day3_gr_190f4849:


    nar "I feel as if a heavy weight's been lifted from my shoulders. I spot Dr. Grette, who's holding a pastry in her mouth."


translate English day3_gr_c505f16b:


    nar "Normally, she would've noticed my arrival right away, but she seems focused on some documents in front of her,"


translate English day3_gr_d1c47700:


    nar "and is busy munching on her treat."


translate English day3_gr_12d2241c:


    pl "Doc?"


translate English day3_gr_12697b6b:


    nar "At the sound of my voice, she whips her head in my direction, her eyes wide in surprise."


translate English day3_gr_ec7a620f:


    nar "She hurriedly jumps up from her seat, papers held in one hand and her other covering her mouth as she swallows the pastry."


translate English day3_gr_793805c7:


    gr "Oh... Well, my word! You again... Hey! Don't you know it's polite to knock before coming in?"


translate English day3_gr_34ddc9c7:


    pl "Sorry, sorry! The door was open so I walked in... Are you in the middle of a break?"


translate English day3_gr_109f9a95:


    gr "Not exactly. Just getting some paperwork sorted!" with sshake


translate English day3_gr_5e8bffc1:


    pl "Heh heh! It doesn't bother me. Whatever it was looked delicious!"


translate English day3_gr_356a16a4:


    gr "Mm... It was. I'm a messy, good-for-nothing doctor..."


translate English day3_gr_94b6337a:


    pl "I was hoping we could talk about a few things, but do you have a moment?"


translate English day3_gr_fbb6db2a:


    gr "Absolutely! I was hoping to have a nice long chat with someone around now."


translate English day3_gr_5a9868ab:


    pl "Great! Our conversations always make me feel better afterward. Oh! Did you make that pastry yourself?"


translate English day3_gr_9e9c55bc:


    gr "I got it from a youngster who I'm always taking care of. "


translate English day3_gr_bda277a8:


    gr "It's from one of the more famous pastry shops in the capital. The buttery biscuit goes perfectly with tea..."


translate English day3_gr_455ecdf1:


    nar "She seems to be mentally recalling the flavor experience as she speaks, an expression of rapture on her face. "


translate English day3_gr_afe8b546:


    nar "Someone as charming as Dr. Grette must get gifts all the time."


translate English day3_gr_1c6ea3d4:


    nar "I've only been here a few days and I've already received quite a number of surprises from her."


translate English day3_gr_acaa064f:


    nar "I've quickly come to associate both warmth and the tempting smell of sweet pastries with her in my head."


translate English day3_gr_f124e49c:


    gr "Oh, but... I'm sorry to say, I'm all out of sweets for today."


translate English day3_gr_7f49e51c:


    pl "Don't worry about it. You got that as a gift, so you should enjoy it."


translate English day3_gr_537941e3:


    gr "But you came all this way. Hmm..."


translate English day3_gr_004326ec:


    gr "Right! There's a little bit left of the apple pie I baked this morning. Want a slice?"


translate English day3_gr_0326f710:


    pl "Heck yeah!"


translate English day3_gr_ddce2982:


    nar "As she places a small slice of apple pie on a plate with a flower painted on it,"


translate English day3_gr_cd2dc48d:


    nar "my senses are once again filled with the scent of cinnamon that I smelled from the open doorway."


translate English day3_gr_6278033d:


    nar "The fork next to the plate has an equally adorable pattern painted on it, making me feel almost like I'm having a pretend tea party. "


translate English day3_gr_ac101d2d:


    nar "The pie melts in your mouth and has just the right amount of sweetness."


translate English day3_gr_a45f5519:


    nar "The excellent flavor reminds me of the pies I used to eat growing up in my hometown."


translate English day3_gr_e183321f:


    nar "It has a calming effect on my downtrodden spirit."


translate English day3_gr_faeeab55:


    gr "How does it taste?"


translate English day3_gr_036af75d:


    pl "Delicious! Maybe one of the best pies I've ever eaten!"


translate English day3_gr_cc3cb04b:


    gr "Oh, gosh! You're such a sweet talker! "


translate English day3_gr_c6ede0b6:


    gr "I'm sorry it's cold. I gave some to the Health Department kiddos not too long ago."


translate English day3_gr_180cc8dd:


    pl "And right around lunch time, too. It's nice of you to give out snacks like this."


translate English day3_gr_e1cd70a7:


    gr "I'm honored. Unfortunately, there's a bunch of folks here who don't appreciate my baking on temple grounds..."


translate English day3_gr_db68ea80:


    gr "Also, I don't share my treats with just anyone, either."


translate English day3_gr_515f608d:


    pl "I'm sure once they try a bite of your cooking, they'll quickly change their minds!"


translate English day3_gr_8dc1130c:


    gr "Heh heh! That's a good idea."


translate English day3_gr_def800e6:


    gr "Now then, I'm all ears for whatever you wanted to talk to me about."


translate English day3_gr_18011c4e:


    pl "I'm sure you're aware, but I was invited to come here as part of the Magic Department."


translate English day3_gr_212f68d7:


    gr "Mm, so I heard."


translate English day3_gr_1e2573e2:


    nar "Wow, I guess everyone here really does know..."


translate English day3_gr_b26a0eef:


    pl "I had a chat with the bishop of the Magic Department a little bit ago."


translate English day3_gr_9d2d9a83:


    gr "Oh, my... Are you okay? He didn't say anything mean to you, did he?"


translate English day3_gr_8d63155a:


    pl "Huh? No, nothing bad happened... Though everyone seems to share the same concern."


translate English day3_gr_8f96fc34:


    gr "That's a relief! Erzsebet has the power and the strong will you would expect the bishop of the Magic Department to hold..."


translate English day3_gr_f43b981f:


    gr "and he has a tendency to speak his mind rather bluntly. He's hurt plenty of youngsters with his words before."


translate English day3_gr_237973ae:


    pl "Really? He can get pretty arrogant. I felt like he was looking down on me the whole time."


translate English day3_gr_5e118302:


    gr "He even snubbed the pastries I made just for him! The epitome of rudeness, if you ask me."


translate English day3_gr_3daf5727:


    pl "So the guy who doesn't like your treats is Eri then?"


translate English day3_gr_0fa39033:


    gr "AHEM! It's still embarrassing for me to talk about, but I know next time will go a lot better."


translate English day3_gr_6bfe35a9:


    gr "Erzsebet tends to have a cup of tea at every meeting. I'll just make a bunch of desserts that I know will compliment the tea he likes perfectly!"


translate English day3_gr_1682b1ea:


    pl "I'm sure you can pull it off! And I'm happy to be your taste tester."


translate English day3_gr_ce8d3f13:


    gr "I'll be sure to make some for you, too, though it might be the failed attempts..."


translate English day3_gr_38c37dea:


    pl "I'm happy to eat whatever you make, failed or otherwise!"


translate English day3_gr_3cd5f7cb:


    pl "Oh, by the way. I had a talk with Brother Enoch after meeting with the bishop. Do you know him? He's also from the Magic Department."


translate English day3_gr_37d1e9c5:


    gr "I do. The guy who's taller than you, right?"


translate English day3_gr_1ddeeef4:


    pl "Yep! And incredibly flamboyant."


translate English day3_gr_62ee05d1:


    gr "I know the one! And what did he have to say to you?"


translate English day3_gr_9c244b83:


    pl "You know how Enoch and his sister Arnie are always together? Well, he was asking me about her."


translate English day3_gr_863d5dff:


    gr "By asking you about her, you mean...?"


translate English day3_gr_c2b995f0:


    pl "You know exactly what I mean!"


translate English day3_gr_c2bcc728:


    gr "Oh my, my, my!"


translate English day3_gr_45b6d8c3:


    nar "She slaps both hands to her cheeks and wriggles in excitement, looking very much like a giggling teenage girl. I'm impressed I managed to get the gist across using as few words as I did."


translate English day3_gr_b259b50d:


    nar "It's happened to me before, too. I figured out Enoch's true feelings despite his obvious attempt at hiding it from me."


translate English day3_gr_dbb0112e:


    nar "Why are people's feelings towards others so easy to decipher? Does their love become more obvious the harder they try to hide it?"


translate English day3_gr_5e05633e:


    gr "He's incredibly polite and well-mannered for being so young along with being super friendly. I always find myself happy to spend time with them."


translate English day3_gr_3f86eaad:


    gr "He always makes a point to say hello to me whenever we see each other and is ready to help out at a moment's notice."


translate English day3_gr_bb431acb:


    pl "He seemed a little intimidating at first, but the more we talked, the better I got to know him. He's actually not a bad guy at all."


translate English day3_gr_83aab5d1:


    gr "*sigh*... Which is exactly why I'm kinda worried. "


translate English day3_gr_25570711:


    gr "The reason why he's so accomodating is because he's been raised to always be aware of how others view you. Most families in the Magic Department are very conservative."


translate English day3_gr_6d7cc4eb:


    pl "Ah-ha... That explains all that family ranking stuff he was talking about."


translate English day3_gr_71ecbb50:


    nar "As I touch upon my memory, Dr. Grette furrows her eyebrows and moans in exasperation."


translate English day3_gr_b725eb6e:


    gr "Discrimination based solely on where a person comes from... "


translate English day3_gr_ae05370d:


    gr "Well, growing up in an environment like that, it's no wonder some of that bias rubbed off on him."


translate English day3_gr_95bc52b4:


    gr "Yet he's the type who can't say what's on his mind."


translate English day3_gr_d420b0ba:


    gr "As a teacher and doctor, I know you're all still kids, so I don't want you purposefully holding back on doing something you want to."


translate English day3_gr_8a08639c:


    pl "Mm-hmm..."


translate English day3_gr_0571cfa3:


    nar "After hearing her explanation, I'm beginning to understand the kind of person he really is."


translate English day3_gr_10099021:


    nar "His feigned embarrassment and exaggerated denial was his attempt at probing for the truth."


translate English day3_gr_87a6fb34:


    pl "You're incredibly perceptive, doc. You gleaned all that after just a few conversations?"


translate English day3_gr_4967c5c7:


    gr "I wouldn't be much of a health care provider if I couldn't do that much, now would I?"


translate English day3_gr_2cb97db1:


    gr "What you youngsters need more than anything is someone more experienced you can trust in."


translate English day3_gr_f1458bde:


    gr "Don't ever forget that there are always folks around who will help you if you ever need it."


translate English day3_gr_736446f8:


    nar "She spits out the words, sounding almost exasperated. It's as if she's urging me to confide in her, to tell her what I'm stressing about."


translate English day3_gr_2ad5b3f8:


    nar "My thoughts return to what happened the night before, but I immediately shut that line of thinking down. I'm finally in a good mood, and I don't want to ruin it."


translate English day3_gr_fca18930:


    nar "I put the final bite of apple pie in my mouth in an attempt at swallowing my troubled memories from last night."


translate English day3_gr_126e6b08:


    nar "But the sting of just a touch too much cinnamon makes my throat hurt."


translate English day3_gr_895bc287:


    pl "Honestly, I didn't expect a doctor like you to also be a competent counselor. Add in your job as part of the Health Department and it sounds like you're a really busy person."


translate English day3_gr_3c42632b:


    gr "Hm? I swear I mentioned it before. I feel like things are slowly ramping up."


translate English day3_gr_73c8c43c:


    gr "...Well, no. To tell you the truth, I'd be lying if I said I'm not swamped."


translate English day3_gr_63c4fac1:


    gr "I've always been happy to work as a counselor of sorts. "


translate English day3_gr_50f1a0ba:


    gr "I don't mind being this busy if it means getting to help the youngsters here with their various life issues. Actually, I'm kind of grateful to be able to do so."


translate English day3_gr_f231d25b:


    pl "Wow... I always thought you were great, but in fact, you are actually incredible. There's not enough words for me to express how I feel!"


translate English day3_gr_8727062a:


    gr "I still have a lot to learn, though. There's times where I feel like I pick up a lot from the interpersonal connections I build and nurture. "


translate English day3_gr_efedc4a9:


    gr "And yet, I simply can't take care of every young person here..."


translate English day3_gr_f61b039a:


    nar "Even with a counselor to talk to, there are plenty of people who don't feel comfortable talking about what bothers them."


translate English day3_gr_fcd5b885:


    nar "All of us feel some degree of shame over our problems and secrets. Many prefer to keep them hidden."


translate English day3_gr_212f3546:


    nar "People lie and obscure the truth--I'm no different."


translate English day3_gr_58b4e0b1:


    pl "So then, did you only start counseling folks after you started working here?"


translate English day3_gr_940456bd:


    gr "Nope! I studied the craft in school. In fact, I left the capital for a bit in order to learn more than I could here."


translate English day3_gr_6f2fc1d1:


    gr "I remember my very first session... It was a little over ten years ago."


translate English day3_gr_af0964cd:


    gr "I'll never forget that day. Ha, it's funny to think how inexperienced I was..."


translate English day3_gr_da664846:


    pl "Ooh! Tales of the doc's youth! Tell me more! Tell me more!"


translate English day3_gr_1b1c6748:


    gr "Eh? Oh, knock it off! I'm honestly embarrassed just mentioning it, though... You're really interested?"


translate English day3_gr_8c324255:


    pl "Of course!"


translate English day3_gr_3f0d364c:


    gr "Well, in that case... ahem..."


translate English day3_gr_4c0960ae:


    nar "She suddenly looks away from me for the first time since I arrived, as if reminiscing on her past."


translate English day3_gr_42175b09:


    nar "It's clear she's looking at something other than the all-too-familiar walls of the infirmary."


translate English day3_gr_b5872de2:


    nar "She's the type who always maintains direct eye contact with whoever's in front of her."


translate English day3_gr_06044d79:


    gr "Let's see... It's already been well over ten years since then."


translate English day3_gr_a08b619f:


    gr "The first person I ever counseled was a young girl."


translate English day3_gr_65a59827:


    gr "Actually, she was a little younger than you are now, [na2]."


translate English day3_gr_615a93ce:


    gr "Her original counselor was a friend of mine. At first, I was a little nervous..."


translate English day3_gr_1c74b97a:


    gr "but as soon as I saw her face, all my anxiety vanished in an instant."


translate English day3_gr_80e61162:


    pl "Because of how cute she was?"


translate English day3_gr_f91de498:


    gr "Ha, exactly! With her smooth skin and long eyelashes, she looked like a doll come to life."


translate English day3_gr_6039501a:


    gr "And her eyes were just as expressionless as one, too."


translate English day3_gr_052ff353:


    gr "At the time, I swore to myself that I'd do whatever I could to help her."


translate English day3_gr_460c0fbb:


    gr "When she referred to me by my title for the first time... well... I'm embarrassed to admit it, but.."


translate English day3_gr_7f532d17:


    gr "Well, I cried."


translate English day3_gr_60de6636:


    pl "And now everyone calls you doc."


translate English day3_gr_9ba0818c:


    gr "You're right, and I can't thank her enough. The person I am today is all because of her."


translate English day3_gr_9224ad3e:


    pl "What was she like?"


translate English day3_gr_8083ae45:


    gr "I obviously can't talk in too much detail about a former patient of mine, "


translate English day3_gr_c8473595:


    gr "but due to an absolutely horrendous accident, she was psychologically traumatized and her memories were a mess."


translate English day3_gr_6c47806e:


    gr "At first, she wasn't ready to open up and didn't talk much."


translate English day3_gr_f1817f4b:


    pl "Uh-huh..."


translate English day3_gr_817f8daf:


    gr "Still, she was such a great kid. She listened to every word I said, and before I knew it, she slowly started confiding in me. "


translate English day3_gr_fd06b967:


    gr "She started with small problems first and worked her way up to more serious ones."


translate English day3_gr_a0c33722:


    gr "Thankfully, she came to rely on me a lot. I was happy to have someone in my life who felt like a younger sister. It almost felt like a stroke of luck..."


translate English day3_gr_c8f9db56:


    pl "But it wasn't luck. It's because of how good you are at connecting with people."


translate English day3_gr_d1df908b:


    pl "Despite not knowing the first thing about this girl,"


translate English day3_gr_2f65edb0:


    pl "I can tell how much you cared just from the way you talk about her."


translate English day3_gr_ed4b49ee:


    pl "You two had a pretty strong emotional connection, huh?"


translate English day3_gr_c2b4363b:


    gr "Come to think of it, you're not much of a talker, either, [na2]. "


translate English day3_gr_5f56b9b5:


    gr "As your doctor, I'm impressed..."


translate English day3_gr_844fa6e1:


    pl "Oh, don't cry, doc! There's a ton of folks here who want you to be happy, but I also prefer seeing a smile on your face."


translate English day3_gr_4869b6cd:


    gr "Of course! With youngsters like you around, I can't help but smile, even when I'm fast asleep!"


translate English day3_gr_2d321fd2:


    pl "Seeing you always makes me feel so much better, too!"


translate English day3_gr_d79c7d5e:


    gr "Heh heh heh... I'm happy that you care about me, but your happiness is what brings me more joy than anything else."


translate English day3_gr_a6b8d65a:


    gr "I'll have a huge smile on my face as long as you guys are happy."


translate English day3_gr_cacf165d:


    gr "If my smile makes you feel better, [na2], then I'm more than happy to oblige you!"


translate English day3_gr_cbf6d2d5:


    pl "Wow! If that's true, then I'll be happy for the rest of my life!"


translate English day3_gr_9eb76d5c:


    gr "That's right, happiness and unhappiness are all connected. It's all dependent on how you feel."


translate English day3_gr_aa0f4e21:


    pl "I really mean it when I say my soul feels lighter whenever I'm with you. I'm actually kind of jealous of the folks in the Health Department..."


translate English day3_gr_6c485f51:


    gr "Goodness, you don't have to be jealous. As long as you're in the temple, you're all my kids. You can come see me whenever you want."


translate English day3_gr_9a1dafd1:


    pl "I really appreciate it. Speaking of which... how's that former patient doing now anyway?"


translate English day3_gr_0b5c5cc5:


    gr "I actually still see her quite often. She's grown into a fine adult."


translate English day3_gr_94f21fb8:


    gr "A wonderful person and gorgeous lady... plus she brings me treats all the time. A very remarkable person."


translate English day3_gr_9eb62332:


    pl "Great! I'm surprised you two are still connected after ten years, though..."


translate English day3_gr_30e4018a:


    pl "Hrm? Wait a sec, you said she brings you treats? Does that mean she works here at the temple?"


translate English day3_gr_f28cee63:


    gr "Oh, my... Heh heh heh! The secrets between us seem to be growing."


translate English day3_gr_edb2cfdb:


    pl "Huh? Seriously?! I want to meet her!"


translate English day3_gr_1bc52cab:


    gr "Maybe you will someday. You know, I have an old friend who's very wise."


translate English day3_gr_0076e4c5:


    gr "They told me once that friendships come and go, but..."


translate English day3_gr_ee27bf13:


    gr "if they're important enough to you and you nurture them, then any relationship can be rekindled."


translate English day3_gr_b97b3193:


    pl "Sounds pretty serious..."


translate English day3_gr_e7941454:


    gr "That's what I thouht at first, but to put it plainly, once a friend, always a friend... or something like that. "


translate English day3_gr_b02b7396:


    gr "Actually, most of my friendships are like that."


translate English day3_gr_61d56110:


    pl "I can see that!"


translate English day3_gr_3e0c920c:


    gr "Right? It's nice always being surrounded by people you know. It makes it easier to have conversations like this."


translate English day3_gr_b11872d0:


    pl "I agree! I love talking with you about all kinds of things."


translate English day3_gr_3ffee4cd:


    gr "How coincidental that we're on the same page! I'm really happy that you brought this up first."


translate English day3_gr_4f6e34dc:


    nar "We lose ourselves in our lighthearted conversation until the chirp of the cuckoo clock on the wall brings us back to reality. The hands of the clock indicate it's already past noon."


translate English day3_gr_d8a1f566:


    gr "I guess I should really get back to work. And you as well, [na2]."


translate English day3_gr_cb5ef90d:


    pl "Yeah. Thanks for everything, doc! I was a little bummed because of the rain, but thanks to you, I'm feeling a lot better."


translate English day3_gr_f5a39677:


    gr "Feel free to stop by whenever you're in the mood to talk with a chatty old lady."


translate English day3_gr_3ec7ebca:


    pl "Hey! I should be the one inviting you to do that."


translate English day3_gr_04056090:


    pl "I actually really love talking with people, but the atmosphere in the temple is so suffocating that I feel like I don't get many chances to do so."


translate English day3_gr_35ce7276:


    gr "Well, talking is my specialty. By the way, what kind of treats do you like, [na2]? I'll be sure to keep some around just for you."


translate English day3_gr_3e7d90bb:


    pl "My favorite snacks? Actually, I'm not really sure. It's not that I dislike them, it's just I haven't had many opportunities to eat them."


translate English day3_gr_9140b9e5:


    pl "Where I'm from, we usually eat dried fruit or just plain toast with butter or jam."


translate English day3_gr_2e235ff4:


    pl "Though that's more like a substitute meal than a snack."


translate English day3_gr_7d418f36:


    gr "Oh, my. I see..."


translate English day3_gr_9baafc5d:


    pl "Which is why I'd prefer if you baked what YOU want to make! And then maybe your favorite snacks will become mine, too, someday."


translate English day3_gr_7cc42191:


    gr "Well, gosh! My, my, my, oh my! You really ARE a sweet talker, [na2]! Thanks to you, I'm more motivated than ever to bake my heart out. Leave everything to me!"


translate English day3_ar_bb8bac5a:


    nar "I come to the training room to see her, but as I stand before the door, my memories of yesterday come back to me."


translate English day3_ar_4504615e:


    nar "All those eyes on me--cautious, wary. The voice that suddenly resounded. It wasn't to the point of being traumatic, but the experience did leave a deep impression on me."


translate English day3_ar_1642d77f:


    nar "The door is just as big as the rest of the building. I'm not sure where to put my hand."


translate English day3_ar_a4930544:


    nar "Also, it's noisy inside. I doubt anyone would hear me if I knocked."


translate English day3_ar_b5aaf294:


    nar "In the end, I'm at a loss. On a whim, I put my ear up to the door, figuring I'd try to guess how many people are inside."


translate English day3_ar_81b2328e:


    nar "As I listen to the faint voices on the other side, the heavy door suddenly opens."


translate English day3_ar_313050c6:


    nar "Surprised, I step back, seeing a priest standing there alone."


translate English day3_ar_82c937c8:


    pl "U-Umm..."


translate English day3_ar_e383032f:


    nar "Crap. He's gotta be suspicious of me since he caught me like that."


translate English day3_ar_cbca7925:


    nar "Surprisingly, though, the priest's voice is bright and clear, despite the veil over his face."


translate English day3_ar_4f605127:


    ex6 "Lord [na]! We've been waiting for you."


translate English day3_ar_b0530705:


    pl "Wait, you have?"


translate English day3_ar_0b87ce77:


    ex6 "Indeed, we have young man. Lady Arne is in the back. I'll show you to her."


translate English day3_ar_188436a1:


    nar "Huh? Wasn't this guy one of the ones gossiping about me yesterday while I was standing right in front of him?"


translate English day3_ar_db4b3e69:


    nar "Still suspicious, I follow him as once again all of the clergyfolk around us stop in their tracks. The mood, however, is entirely different from the previous time this happened to me."


translate English day3_ar_b6cf7db9:


    nar "I hear no voices at all. Instead, every time I look at someone, they only offer a silent bow. Is it because of how she yelled at them?"


translate English day3_ar_cb608f2a:


    nar "The sudden change in their attitude is too awkward to even think about, so I set my eyes ahead and walk straight without looking at anyone."


translate English day3_ar_86db6560:


    nar "Eventually, my eyes meet with Arnie's."


translate English day3_ar_9b6c42bf:


    nar "I stop in front of her, in the center of the unspeaking onlookers. It makes me feel strangely nervous, unlike yesterday."


translate English day3_ar_bf069dd4:


    nar "It's like this whole thing is a scene in a stage play, orchestrated by some invisible director."


translate English day3_ar_906b3bfb:


    ar "Good morning, Brother [na2]. It is truly an honor to be able to meet you again."


translate English day3_ar_a384267d:


    pl "Well, it seems like you're busy... I feel kind of bad for interrupting. Just like yesterday."


translate English day3_ar_71e26d55:


    nar "The long eyelashes ringing her eyelids move up and down. The expression on her immaculate face seems troubled somehow."


translate English day3_ar_eddb4a1a:


    ar "In general, those of the Magic Department give group action the utmost importance. I sincerely apologize for not being able to make time for you individually."


translate English day3_ar_0b23f241:


    pl "Hey, no need for apologies! It's my fault for coming by to hang out."


translate English day3_ar_d82d7188:


    ar "Would you mind waiting a short while? I shall prepare some tea forthwith, and--"


translate English day3_ar_84c69d30:


    pl "No, you seem busy, so I'm just going to watch you work for today."


translate English day3_ar_4ecae678:


    ar "But--"


translate English day3_ar_c17fc810:


    pl "I said don't worry about it. After all, this is what a trainee is supposed to do, right?"


translate English day3_ar_6462ea91:


    nar "I tried to put all my energy into my replies, but she still looks unconvinced as she glances between me and the other clergyfolk."


translate English day3_ar_aed5673f:


    nar "Then, seeming to make up her mind, she looks straight at me."


translate English day3_ar_4fbcb15c:


    ar "Understood... However, I would ask that you remain by my side unless I am personally giving an example to them."


translate English day3_ar_d7104114:


    pl "Huh? You mean you want me to watch everyone train?"


translate English day3_ar_09deb2c9:


    ar "Yes, I do."


translate English day3_ar_e92c78fc:


    pl "Well... That's fine by me. I just hope I don't get in the way."


translate English day3_ar_21bd6807:


    ar "Your consideration for my unconscionable words is much appreciated."


translate English day3_ar_5f700746:


    nar "Arne Alternata--eldest daughter of the Alternata family, a famous one in the capital."


translate English day3_ar_ff4165fe:


    nar "She's the niece of Erzsebet, the main bishop of the Magic Department, and works as an auxiliary bishop alongside her younger brother, Enoch Apis."


translate English day3_ar_fa5ceafd:


    nar "That's pretty much all I know about her. And yet... I'm engaged to her? Is this some awful capital prank I'm too rustic to understand?"


translate English day3_ar_b1328e44:


    ar "Is something the matter?"


translate English day3_ar_ea1bec62:


    pl "Huh? Oh, er... Just wondering. Where's Enoch at?"


translate English day3_ar_fa51dc28:


    ar "He has not yet arrived. He must be working on a different task. He has the most freedom of anyone serving the Magic Department."


translate English day3_ar_e06d2ebf:


    pl "Yeah, this place does seem different compared to the other departments. And he's an auxiliary bishop, huh? That's funny."


translate English day3_ar_d6e155a2:


    ar "...Brother [na2], have you exchanged words with Enoch elsewhere?"


translate English day3_ar_aa0be3f3:


    pl "I mean... Yeah, but just a little before I came here."


translate English day3_ar_9d24346a:


    ar "Ah, so I see..."


translate English day3_ar_5083391c:


    pl "Why?"


translate English day3_ar_bdc4326f:


    ar "I apologize. I was just happy that the two of you have gotten to know each other better."


translate English day3_ar_d99e9289:


    pl "What? Me and him?"


translate English day3_ar_06a0efd9:


    ar "The way you speak of him shows that you've gotten closer."


translate English day3_ar_7bd226e6:


    pl "Oh. I see..."


translate English day3_ar_2749fdf5:


    ar "Unlike me, Enoch has excellent people skills and is the optimal person for talking to others."


translate English day3_ar_91526cf0:


    ar "Keep him at your side for I'm sure he will be a boon to you, Brother."


translate English day3_ar_ab4f81a3:


    pl "Ahaha..."


translate English day3_ar_7834ccf5:


    ar "...And speaking honestly, you would have a good influence on him as well."


translate English day3_ar_3c43c7d6:


    pl "You mean me and him making friends?"


translate English day3_ar_da4d75f8:


    ar "That I do. He visited our family when he was very young. I was the same age at the time. He helped me in many things."


translate English day3_ar_1d9c3752:


    ar "Even after his coming-of-age ceremony, he followed me straight to this temple to continue supporting me."


translate English day3_ar_97899ee4:


    ar "In that time, not once has he expressed any dissatisfaction towards me... Ah, but he is originally someone who highly regards deepening bonds and relationships."


translate English day3_ar_6cd08990:


    ar "He says his life here isn't suffocating, though I suspect that is probably a white lie meant to comfort me, as well as others."


translate English day3_ar_69435604:


    pl "Huh."


translate English day3_ar_a7854fde:


    ar "That is why I believe talking to someone as free-spirited as you will have a positive effect on him."


translate English day3_ar_a960448e:


    pl "You really like him, huh?"


translate English day3_ar_f2ecb4f4:


    ar "Of course. He is my family, and I am proud of that."


translate English day3_ar_95761d2c:


    nar "Not only is he important to Arnie, she's proud of him. I've never once felt that way toward my own family."


translate English day3_ar_5b13f4b4:


    nar "I loved my family enough, but the one I'm proud of is myself--for not letting my mind be sullied by old-fashioned traditions."


translate English day3_ar_34c33140:


    nar "I'm self-centered, but they're so upright and adhere to rules. Wouldn't I be more like a poison than an aid?"


translate English day3_ar_bac07947:


    pl "But the way I perceived it, Enoch is really proud of being able to be with you."


translate English day3_ar_8f5330e2:


    ar "Truly?"


translate English day3_ar_51e1f4ab:


    pl "Yeah. So I think he'd be surprised to hear you feel the same way. You're such a good family!"


translate English day3_ar_f4735075:


    ar "What are you saying? Aren't you also family, Brother [na2]?"


translate English day3_ar_9a488eec:


    pl "Me...?"


translate English day3_ar_642fcf59:


    nar "I suddenly get goosebumps. But they're not the unpleasant, revolted kind. That's how I've felt all day, so I know right away this is a different feeling entirely."


translate English day3_ar_9553646d:


    nar "It feels like a frost has come over my heart and spine. That isn't at all like the goosebumps I got before."


translate English day3_ar_ba6528d9:


    nar "Just as I try to ask her the question, two priests approach and bow to greet Arnie. Have they finished up?"


translate English day3_ar_d1137af9:


    ar "Good work. Both of your skills have improved much."


translate English day3_ar_927a9be4:


    nar "Despite how few words she uses, the priests' faces light up. Then, one at a time, she explains things like their posture, breathing, and motions."


translate English day3_ar_32a9c431:


    nar "The two priests nod, one after another, as they mimic the way Arnie moves her arms and legs, showing that they're really listening."


translate English day3_ar_dfe6bf49:


    ar "Ah, I noticed you pull your left ankle back, just for a moment. Did you push yourself too hard during your work this morning?"


translate English day3_ar_60f87b5e:


    nar "I quickly lose interest in what they're saying and stop listening, but those words shock me."


translate English day3_ar_679b655b:


    nar "She's been talking to me the whole time. When did she have time to even see that?"


translate English day3_ar_c41a26a5:


    nar "Eventually the two priests part ways. And yet, when I look closely, they seem to be bowing in my direction as well. "


translate English day3_ar_29ef387a:


    nar "Embarrassed at having quietly withdrawn before, I find myself lowering my own head to them."


translate English day3_ar_83b539a5:


    ar "Pardon me for interrupting our conversation."


translate English day3_ar_f67189b2:


    pl "Arnie, you're amazing. Were you watching them while talking to me?"


translate English day3_ar_e3d4934e:


    ar "Of course. Even while training, they are passionate, earnest, and serious about sparring."


translate English day3_ar_29354dfe:


    ar "The least I can do in return is to be just as serious with them."


translate English day3_ar_de080c95:


    pl "Huh..."


translate English day3_ar_b0e68b88:


    ar "That goes for you too, Brother [na2]. "


translate English day3_ar_fb63c2c0:


    ar "You came here to speak with me, and not to anyone else here... "


translate English day3_ar_ebd257ad:


    ar "I cannot allow myself to miss even a single syllable of what you're saying."


translate English day3_ar_3fed3bcf:


    pl "It's great that a lot of people are interested in you and support you, but... Doesn't it ever get difficult to handle all of it?"


translate English day3_ar_c4370c5e:


    ar "I am yet inexperienced, but if I receive their support out of necessity, should I not be thankful for it?"


translate English day3_ar_1e26f940:


    pl "...But if you're doing two things at once like this, don't you still have to prioritize things?"


translate English day3_ar_6675c52a:


    ar "Yes, I do."


translate English day3_ar_41a84da0:


    pl "What's the priority order usually like?"


translate English day3_ar_7e350ace:


    ar "Hmm... I would say that in this training room, my priorities in order are everyone's safety, the morale of the priests, and then the training itself."


translate English day3_ar_49710fcd:


    pl "Oh, so raising morale is pretty high up on your list, huh?"


translate English day3_ar_91f766fa:


    ar "Yes. Improving physical abilities is important, but maintaining one's mental fortitude is even more so."


translate English day3_ar_dcb0356d:


    ar "If one's focus wanes or one's self-esteem lessens, that will naturally lead to a neglect of training, will it not?"


translate English day3_ar_4705de2f:


    pl "I guess no matter what it is, you've gotta have that enthusiasm, huh?"


translate English day3_ar_a80e8133:


    nar "Is that why she prioritized me, the \"sudden guest,\" yesterday?"


translate English day3_ar_9c908869:


    nar "The priests probably can't focus on training with me being an unknown outsider to them."


translate English day3_ar_bebcac0a:


    nar "She's a wise person. She answers all my questions as though she already had the answers and never once does she seem flustered."


translate English day3_ar_deb5734c:


    pl "Well, then..."


translate English day3_ar_498307da:


    pl "If you had to pick between Enoch or me, who would you choose?"


translate English day3_ar_82b645ea:


    nar "I'm not sure why I asked that completely wild question."


translate English day3_ar_a795a2a5:


    nar "I should have just made a little joke like I always do. But now everything feels heavier, and I don't know how to fix it. It's because of my bad mood."


translate English day3_ar_d4a28b8f:


    nar "Though the words that came out of my mouth surprised me, her reaction surprises me even more."


translate English day3_ar_5714c887:


    ar "Heh heh... Ahahaha!"


translate English day3_ar_b082c680:


    nar "Her quiet face suddenly breaks out into laughter. It's so unexpected it snaps me right out of my reverie."


translate English day3_ar_7181370e:


    pl "Hey... Don't try to get out of it by laughing!~"


translate English day3_ar_2505a80d:


    ar "I'm sorry for my frivolous, embarrasing behavior. However... "


translate English day3_ar_56fa0047:


    ar "To be in a position where I can worry about something like that? I must be a happy woman indeed. The thought made me laugh. Heh heh heh. I am sorry, though."


translate English day3_ar_eb1e660c:


    pl "..."


translate English day3_ar_637ac134:


    ar "Well... Yes, this is a bit of a quandary."


translate English day3_ar_bf2b4fea:


    pl "Right?"


translate English day3_ar_860a37ae:


    ar "What do you think, Brother?"


translate English day3_ar_1df1ee5c:


    pl "Huh? What do you mean?"


translate English day3_ar_2cd84f18:


    ar "In this situation, which matter would you want me to prioritize?"


translate English day3_ar_2fb4fb85:


    pl "...You're asking me? Well... Obviously I'd want you to prioritize me."


translate English day3_ar_e1dbda07:


    ar "Then prioritize you I shall."


translate English day3_ar_e2cd884e:


    pl "What...?! Really?"


translate English day3_ar_aafd1f9e:


    ar "Yes. I want to listen to your desires and grant them if possible. To do so brings me great joy."


translate English day3_ar_0a19a567:


    pl "But your brother might get lonely! He'll wonder who the heck upstaged him!"


translate English day3_ar_61e02ebc:


    ar "Would he now? I don't think so."


translate English day3_ar_9b166f06:


    pl "You can only say that because you don't understand people's hearts."


translate English day3_ar_c068a5e1:


    ar "Sometimes, one's heart must be displayed, not spoken of. And I am always sincere when it comes to my siblings."


translate English day3_ar_071313dd:


    ar "It is the least I can do to thank them for only speaking the truth during our conversations."


translate English day3_ar_08f92aeb:


    nar "After she speaks, she looks back at the priests again. She definitely doesn't understand the true nature of people's hearts. Who would ever only tell the truth?"


translate English day3_ar_2ce985e5:


    nar "Her convenient words are clearly not meant to be quibbling. She's even showing her back to me now."


translate English day3_ar_6f9cb1d1:


    nar "It's terrifying, thinking about her kindness having no reason behind it."


translate English day3_ar_f1b7d0d7:


    nar "At this point, it would be better just to know the actual reason."


translate English day3_ar_635908bc:


    ar "I apologize for taking so long."


translate English day3_ar_ea22e7d4:


    pl "Huh? Wait, you're done already?"


translate English day3_ar_a26efa74:


    ar "I've simply explained the important, core concepts. This means we won't have to speak for too long."


translate English day3_ar_089afe99:


    pl "Wait, you can do that? If you could do something so smart, how come you didn't until just now?"


translate English day3_ar_393bbe5d:


    ar "Because until just now, I didn't have anyone beside me who would wait until my words were finished."


translate English day3_ar_f8e1e87d:


    pl "Whoa..."


translate English day3_ar_109b9bc4:


    nar "I gasp a little without meaning to, but quickly collect myself."


translate English day3_ar_f4097d89:


    pl "That's... Well, I'm honored."


translate English day3_ar_23eb6cc1:


    ar "The honor is all mine."


translate English day3_ar_e0d9bbc6:


    pl "There's something I wanted to ask you..."


translate English day3_ar_14d26731:


    ar "What is it?"


translate English day3_ar_fe8af0ec:


    pl "Well, I'd rather not ask you in front of so many people. Could we go somewhere else?"


translate English day3_ar_ebe812d1:


    nar "She blinks at my glum face, and after a moment, gives another casual response."


translate English day3_ar_1dd48a01:


    ar "Understood."


translate English day3_ar_d2e8fd02:


    nar "Understood? How far is she going to let me push her? It's only the two of us in the hot-water room."


translate English day3_ar_54349d90:


    ar "Would you like some tea?"


translate English day3_ar_045abbd2:


    pl "No, I'm fine. I don't want to bother you too much."


translate English day3_ar_fceecf0c:


    ar "Understood."


translate English day3_ar_bbd7d183:


    nar "She modestly takes a seat across from me. Everything she does is so mysterious. Plus, she looks so much like the person from before that it's startling."


translate English day3_ar_d4bcc83f:


    nar "And he's in the form of a child--yet I still realized how much they resemble each other right away."


translate English day3_ar_30fd3ef2:


    nar "His words come to mind again."


translate English day3_ar_3aef3f5a:


    pl "You, uh... You know I talked to the main bishop of the Magic Department today, right?"


translate English day3_ar_5a8d86ab:


    ar "Yes... I was told as much. Was there some sort of problem...?"


translate English day3_ar_2f0b3da0:


    pl "I mean, maybe it's not a problem, per se..."


translate English day3_ar_ef38910a:


    nar "I scratch at my hair pointlessly. Going through this same problem over and over again is making my head hurt."


translate English day3_ar_6eed40f0:


    pl "And I'm sorry if I'm making a big deal out of something silly, but... Do you know anything about the marriage?"


translate English day3_ar_f46d97e8:


    ar "The marriage..."


translate English day3_ar_b264c553:


    nar "She repeats the words softly as if just hearing them. My face feels like it's going to erupt into flame."


translate English day3_ar_4ff572b9:


    nar "But that eventually subsides when her face, which has been so calm this entire time, steadily takes on a more glum look."


translate English day3_ar_2c376fb4:


    ar "...I see. You've finally heard about that. Just today..."


translate English day3_ar_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "......"


translate English day3_ar_5fedeb64:


    nar "So she did know--right from the start. And maybe this is why the other priests' attitudes towards me are so much more positive today..."


translate English day3_ar_4a70d3c4:


    pl "I didn't actually get much more of an explanation, so I was hoping you could go into more detail."


translate English day3_ar_8e6f06dd:


    ar "Of course. It delves into matters involving our family, however. Is that alright with you?"


translate English day3_ar_a6861765:


    pl "Yep, fine by me."


translate English day3_ar_4bbfa100:


    ar "Very well then."


translate English day3_ar_f88b14e2:


    nar "She nods and gives a small sigh."


translate English day3_ar_9f4e93f6:


    ar "One thing that sets the Magic Department apart from the others at the temple is that we're all family, but... Do you know why that is?"


translate English day3_ar_3d50d544:


    pl "You mentioned that yesterday, but now that I think of it, you didn't really go into detail."


translate English day3_ar_11346390:


    ar "We mages all come from a very old, traditional family lineage. "


translate English day3_ar_6de4ace8:


    ar "The families themselves have long since branched out, but we all come from the same roots."


translate English day3_ar_e7791b6a:


    pl "The same roots? Then you weren't just trying to say you have tight bonds--you mean all mages are actually related to each other?"


translate English day3_ar_58192263:


    ar "Yes and that is the true tradition of our mage family."


translate English day3_ar_63489b69:


    pl "Hmm... I mean, I thought the priests' faces all looked equally scary, but..."


translate English day3_ar_e0e6c9d1:


    ar "Oh, did that surprise you?"


translate English day3_ar_2605b56e:


    pl "Eh, not really. Everyone was basically one big family in the village I used to live in too--we all had the same blood in us."


translate English day3_ar_667f86a0:


    ar "I'm relieved to hear it wasn't too much of a shock for you."


translate English day3_ar_8c78be66:


    pl "So, uh... Why bring me in? I'm a total stranger."


translate English day3_ar_647b214c:


    ar "I believe my uncle explained this, but you have the blood of mages in you as well, Brother."


translate English day3_ar_bd2271c5:


    pl "That's the part I understood the least..."


translate English day3_ar_e2e43802:


    ar "Mages have gone back for many, many generations. Long ago, there were many of us. "


translate English day3_ar_6b94d878:


    ar "Plenty of them lived outside the capital as well... One of those is your ancestor, Brother."


translate English day3_ar_cba8df6d:


    nar "Essentially all the boys my age at my village died out. "


translate English day3_ar_033ac321:


    nar "That's why the adults never gave up on teaching me, even though they didn't take kindly to how weird I was or how much trouble I caused."


translate English day3_ar_224c70be:


    nar "But that isn't enough to explain *this*."


translate English day3_ar_303ceccf:


    pl "There must be plenty of mages in the capital. Why me?"


translate English day3_ar_ff53ee0c:


    pl "I don't have that many stigmata, and you don't know for sure I carry mage blood, do you?"


translate English day3_ar_2b72eb48:


    ar "...In order to explain that, I must first tell you about my uncle."


translate English day3_ar_d030ad81:


    pl "The main bishop of the Magic Department?"


translate English day3_ar_dc9a6a07:


    ar "Yes. People often call him cold and conservative, but..."


translate English day3_ar_6df71650:


    ar "He assumed the position at a young age, and now grapples with a great many problems."


translate English day3_ar_66c64522:


    ar "He stressed the need to reform our current system of marriage between those closely related. That led him to invite an outsider into the family."


translate English day3_ar_21786d15:


    pl "He did...?"


translate English day3_ar_071bf304:


    ar "That is most likely why he assigned you to the Cleanup Department at first--to keep you a secret."


translate English day3_ar_c61b406e:


    ar "Because what my uncle is doing right now is tantamount to outright rebellion against our family."


translate English day3_ar_edd67a4c:


    pl "Is that why he even kept it a secret from me?"


translate English day3_ar_deb2473b:


    nar "She bites her lip and hangs her head, lowering it until her face is out of sight. "


translate English day3_ar_41e31584:


    nar "Her black hair flows down underneath the table."


translate English day3_ar_63eb7825:


    ar "I'm sorry, Brother."


translate English day3_ar_ba45bd66:


    nar "After she says that, it makes sense. She's apologizing to me right now."


translate English day3_ar_041fe204:


    ar "I have essentially lured you here due to personal circumstances. I am so utterly ashamed of myself..."


translate English day3_ar_2c2a38f8:


    ar "I will understand if you look coldly upon me after this. From the very depths of my heart, I apologize."


translate English day3_ar_f30b0d40:


    nar "Like an indistinct dream that hasn't felt real until this moment, what she's saying passes through my mind, causing me to pay attention."


translate English day3_ar_5513b85d:


    nar "Her serious, grave voice is shaking as she boldly defends her position, which shocks me. That resounds in my mind more than the parts"


translate English day3_ar_44ae4f56:


    nar "about reforming their family or taking advantage of me."


translate English day3_ar_87caf442:


    nar "A warm trickle of liquid drips down my cheek. Surprised, I put a hand to it and find it's not a tear, but a droplet of sweat. Why did I think it was a tear?"


translate English day3_ar_75b587a4:


    pl "Settle down, Arnie! You don't need to apologize--I really don't mind it!"


translate English day3_ar_386575c0:


    pl "I was just a little surprised, that's all... Come on, stop bowing, alright?"


translate English day3_ar_1bf9b6fd:


    nar "My nervously strained voice is hoarse. A moment later, only the sound of breathing--though I don't know whose--permeates this forlorn space. She slowly looks up."


translate English day3_ar_85ba2474:


    nar "I feel another chill in my heart as I look at her shadowed face, but seeing no moisture in the corners of her deep eyes sets my mind at ease."


translate English day3_ar_b64d2cfb:


    pl "I'll be honest... I'm still confused about this, and I'm not prepared to accept it, either, but... But I do still want to be friends with you."


translate English day3_ar_c3dd08b4:


    pl "For today, I just wanted to ask about what I didn't know."


translate English day3_ar_f64466f1:


    ar "......"


translate English day3_ar_382360f6:


    pl "So... I'm actually thankful because you only told me the truth."


translate English day3_ar_fe6ec39f:


    ar "You would find it in yourself to forgive someone like me...?"


translate English day3_ar_9e588106:


    pl "Forgive? I wasn't mad to begin with."


translate English day3_ar_15ca6e78:


    pl "I'm the one who said he wanted to work in the capital. You didn't see me treating you or anyone else in a mean way, right?"


translate English day3_ar_6461795c:


    nar "She nods, eyes still shut tight. It looks more like she convinced herself rather than try to answer me."


translate English day3_ar_484623ae:


    ar "If you have any requests at all, I will hear them. I swear on the name of Arne Alternata that I will do my utmost to support you."


translate English day3_ar_1ed28955:


    nar "Her voice is steady, her posture is straight and true, and her eyes are focused on me. That actually makes me anxious."


translate English day3_ar_7d02574f:


    pl "Are you alright, Arnie? Did none of this bother you when you first heard it?"


translate English day3_ar_8e28570f:


    ar "I owe my uncle my life."


translate English day3_ar_c6f62e28:


    ar "I may be unworthy of him, and of the future of our family, but if I am able to do anything to help them... I can imagine no greater honor."


translate English day3_ar_07edbb98:


    nar "Her family's honor... That makes me think of another awkward question, but I decide not to ask it. "


translate English day3_ar_11e609b2:


    nar "Because as she told me that, her expression was the most comfortable I'd seen from her all day."


translate English day3_ar_76f5ad4f:


    nar "I might not understand it, but for her, devoting herself to her family is a source of great happiness. Family, huh..."


translate English day3_ar_89368ba6:


    pl "I wonder if I could ever really become family to you."


translate English day3_ar_cd5fbcdb:


    ar "I may not have known your face or your personality before meeting you... But I did at least have your name from the start--"


translate English day3_ar_6afd53c2:


    ar "and that name is Brother."


translate English day3_ar_abfde96e:


    ar "And as a brother, I have considered you a new member of my family since before we met."


translate English day3_ar_0e352896:


    nar "The two of us leave the room alone, where we're met with the usual footsteps and shouts of the priests honing their talents."


translate English day3_ar_6eb63e70:


    nar "My mind is refreshed now that I've left, but it also feels somehow gloomy. I don't feel betrayed, and I don't feel rejection towards her either."


translate English day3_ar_34059a02:


    nar "But was it really the right choice to ask her about it personally? To attach a reason to her kindness?"


translate English day3_ar_076a4e98:


    nar "Man, I've been really unlucky today."


translate English day3_rs_2183b76d:


    nar "I come to visit the library again, and just like yesterday, I don't see anyone around."


translate English day3_rs_ffe08b67:


    nar "I keep checking behind me, but that librarian lady who talked to me out of the blue is nowhere to be seen."


translate English day3_rs_9b74a04c:


    nar "I wonder who that girl I met yesterday is. "


translate English day3_rs_76061d1e:


    nar "At this point, that little door tucked away in the corner of the quiet library is a matter of interest to me. It weighs on my mind too much to let me just pass it by."


translate English day3_rs_8b29b0a7:


    nar "I slowly open the door, and as if in response to my hopes, the girl from yesterday is inside."


translate English day3_rs_794c3d63:


    nar "She's lying down, completely still, with her hands joined on top of her stomach. She left a book open next to her."


translate English day3_rs_1178bfd2:


    pl "Heeeeey, Rose. Are you asleep?"


translate English day3_rs_03323201:


    rs "Rose is taking a break."


translate English day3_rs_333ba8d8:


    nar "Taking care not to step on her pink hair, which has fallen from where she lays to the floor, I pick up the book."


translate English day3_rs_915585e2:


    nar "It has a yellow cover, with a forest of flowers and trees on it, and on the inside, the sentences are all simple. It's a children's book I happened to run across back home."


translate English day3_rs_a2da6c7f:


    pl "You need a break from reading a picture book...?"


translate English day3_rs_5488ddd2:


    rs "Just how much brain power do you think it takes to create a new story?"


translate English day3_rs_9fb637dc:


    pl "Wh-What?"


translate English day3_rs_7e9c9b27:


    rs "Studies have shown that we only use approximately 48%% of our brain power, answered Rose. Sadly, humans tend to have deeper interest on things that are incomplete."


translate English day3_rs_f3432d89:


    rs "When a story is put into a book, it is the job of the reader to think about all other variables, announced Rose."


translate English day3_rs_f12568d4:


    pl "So basically, you mean... people are free to imagine whatever they want?"


translate English day3_rs_6beb8706:


    rs "Example 1. How did the princess reunite with the prince?"


translate English day3_rs_18b75f60:


    pl "Huh? I wouldn't really know, but... Maybe because they hadn't forgotten about one another?"


translate English day3_rs_24783204:


    rs "Let's break that down further to example 1-1. Why did they cry after reuniting?"


translate English day3_rs_c7d6021a:


    pl "Because they loved each other?"


translate English day3_rs_8799ac57:


    rs "Example 2. Then why was the witch punished?"


translate English day3_rs_560c373c:


    pl "Hmm..."


translate English day3_rs_182e8dcd:


    rs "Go back to Example 1-2. Why was there love between them?"


translate English day3_rs_f460e19b:


    pl "Uh, like I said, I haven't read this book, so I wouldn't know."


translate English day3_rs_61a112dd:


    nar "Suddenly, Rose stops talking. She looks at me without moving her head."


translate English day3_rs_1b5756bd:


    rs "Wait... Who are you?"


translate English day3_rs_c18df958:


    pl "You're just asking that NOW?"


translate English day3_rs_606e438b:


    rs "How did you get in here?"


translate English day3_rs_0895dbaa:


    pl "I opened the door."


translate English day3_rs_f1558622:


    rs "Why are you calling Rose, by the way?"


translate English day3_rs_c065e531:


    pl "You said your name was Rose yesterday, remember? And you keep referring to yourself in the third person, so..."


translate English day3_rs_6d89cb19:


    rs "Ugh, incomprehensible..."


translate English day3_rs_d9225eec:


    nar "I return the book to the shelf, then take a look around the room. Seems like a pretty ordinary office to me."


translate English day3_rs_2b789c0f:


    nar "Shiny gold and silver trophies lined with a layer of dust adorn the walls, and the bookshelf is crammed full of books and documents."


translate English day3_rs_82f167e4:


    nar "Normally, the sight by itself would calm you down, but the multicolored blanket and zabuton on the floor ruin the image."


translate English day3_rs_c3b2d937:


    nar "They mark this room as belonging to her."


translate English day3_rs_8690084e:


    rs "Get out. You're not supposed to be here. Not only have you entered suddenly and without permission, you have even touched things, Rose exclaimed, clearly flustered."


translate English day3_rs_52dccdb2:


    pl "Oh... Yeah, I guess it is like that, huh? Sorry! Is this your room?"


translate English day3_rs_474f46bd:


    nar "She stops talking in an unnatural way. It was a simple question, but all she does is stare at me and blink."


translate English day3_rs_7378c2eb:


    pl "Why are you here, anyway?"


translate English day3_rs_9be1ae57:


    rs "Because Rose is permitted to be here."


translate English day3_rs_f2e79e01:


    pl "You mean... you can't leave?"


translate English day3_rs_c8b4d586:


    rs "Humans all have a space where they're permitted to be. Your space is just a little bigger than Rose's. Don't let it get to your head."


translate English day3_rs_23e43221:


    pl "I wasn't, but... Why, though? Did someone tell you to stay in here?"


translate English day3_rs_c23d0e64:


    rs "You ask a lot of questions. If you want an answer to them, then first give clear answers the the ones Rose asked! Who are you?"


translate English day3_rs_b81224dc:


    pl "Oh, right, I haven't said that yet. I'm [na], the promising new guy in the Cleanup Department! "


translate English day3_rs_1ff9e39a:


    pl "I'm soon to be the most popular person in the temple, so you could probably get a lot out of being friends with me, you know."


translate English day3_rs_bf0347bd:


    rs "It is said that those with incredible arrogance usually end up digging their own graves."


translate English day3_rs_70965428:


    pl "I've got incredible modesty, actually, so no need to worry about that."


translate English day3_rs_23976ea3:


    nar "She sits up, giving me a good look at her. "


translate English day3_rs_448b0963:


    nar "Judging from her clothing and the situation, she's probably a bishop of the Academics Department. What sort of work does she do?"


translate English day3_rs_4ded04c7:


    nar "According to Maya, the department is like a big team of really smart researchers."


translate English day3_rs_96ee18f9:


    rs "Why are you here, [na], Promising New Guy In the Cleanup Department?"


translate English day3_rs_c5d0c56f:


    pl "Because the door was open. Also, I saw the room's master lying on the floor."


translate English day3_rs_68fdf1b6:


    rs "Then you're a careless one for sure."


translate English day3_rs_d4cfba89:


    pl "You got me there!"


translate English day3_rs_68633c32:


    rs "Why have you come here, [na], Promising New Guy In the Cleanup Department?"


translate English day3_rs_5dbd9007:


    pl "To read books in the library, obviously. Also, while I'm glad you're rolling with the title I gave myself, you don't have to call me by it every time."


translate English day3_rs_be5baf7c:


    rs "Your answer is quite inadequate, decided Rose."


translate English day3_rs_d674df7e:


    rs "If that is true, why are you not reading a book quietly in the library instead of standing around in here?"


translate English day3_rs_1cea0470:


    pl "I don't mean to answer a question with another question, but... Is that like, a verbal tic, or do you just enjoy talking like that?"


translate English day3_rs_35d52ddc:


    rs "Don't answer a question with another question! yelled Rose angrily." with sshake


translate English day3_rs_6e96a7d9:


    pl "But it's no fun just answering one question after another! I'm so curious it's making me forget them all."


translate English day3_rs_c318aa05:


    rs "Rose will give you an example of how to answer a question. Rose will express herself in a way that will convey Rose's will to you."


translate English day3_rs_d1f111ac:


    rs "Feelings, words, actions, and intentions must be clarified before they are understood. Otherwise, they will slowly lose their meaning, even for one such as Rose."


translate English day3_rs_edbcaf31:


    pl "Yeah, you don't seem the type to be able to read expressions or really talk much at all, so I guess you'd need to do that, huh?"


translate English day3_rs_f5f050ef:


    rs "Now answer Rose's question."


translate English day3_rs_9efe85bb:


    pl "Alright, alright, don't rush me... "


translate English day3_rs_4f618dfa:


    pl "A librarian here told me I could visit whenever I wanted, "


translate English day3_rs_cef265c2:


    pl "but you seemed kind of neat when I happened to bump into you, so I got curious and decided to stop by. That's all."


translate English day3_rs_bc5fb0a3:


    rs "...Another inadequate response."


translate English day3_rs_2132415d:


    pl "But I followed the example you gave me, like, perfectly."


translate English day3_rs_3e2cd8f7:


    rs "Rose at least never did anything so shameful as try and get out of a situation by lying."


translate English day3_rs_5d07052b:


    pl "I'm not lying! How else am I supposed to explain this? "


translate English day3_rs_4befbc1c:


    pl "You probably only think that because you forgot who I was..."


translate English day3_rs_7e700228:


    rs "I did not forget."


translate English day3_rs_81aacc68:


    pl "Huh? Then what was all that before?"


translate English day3_rs_09a51d07:


    rs "I searched my memories of that time, but was unable to find a response to who you are and why you are here."


translate English day3_rs_215d06c5:


    nar "That was a weird answer. Sensible and total nonsense. I'm amazed at how she can do both at once."


translate English day3_rs_864acb90:


    pl "Anyway, you know now, right? I'm [na], from the Cleanup Department, and I came in here on a whim because the door wasn't closed!"


translate English day3_rs_de84bf6c:


    rs "Wait. Rose still has many questions, but she will now attempt to obtain the answer to the foremost one. "


translate English day3_rs_8c13fadb:


    rs "What did you mean by the comment \"you seemed kind of neat?\""


translate English day3_rs_e172af92:


    pl "I feel like that's not something that needs an explanation..."


translate English day3_rs_8e34a125:


    rs "Well, I demand an explanation."


translate English day3_rs_8c730acb:


    pl "How do I put this? Hmm... You know what you said before about people being attracted to incomplete stories?"


translate English day3_rs_632d1ae1:


    pl "You mean like how plot holes get people's curiosity and creative juices flowing, right? You interested me in the same way."


translate English day3_rs_6d4a3cb8:


    rs "Then you're saying Rose is incomplete...!"


translate English day3_rs_bb6dbae0:


    pl "No, I was just quoting you. I didn't mean to put it like that, but... I guess it's something similar."


translate English day3_rs_4cc8210e:


    rs "In that case... What more does Rose need to be complete?"


translate English day3_rs_f0ba8578:


    pl "Hey, don't get all down on me! Everyone lacks something, you know? "


translate English day3_rs_4ab3d960:


    pl "The best way to get it is by meeting people and talking to them."


translate English day3_rs_2a42c348:


    rs "Your reasoning being...?"


translate English day3_rs_1f1f830b:


    pl "Well, it's simple. Holing up in a place like this isn't going to change anything."


translate English day3_rs_a8a65139:


    pl "And if someone is interested in you, that's a good chance right in front of you. Opportunities like these don't come around very often, you know."


translate English day3_rs_ed50c3d7:


    rs "Hmm."


translate English day3_rs_01d08807:


    nar "Thinking about it, my blathering does sound kind of dubious. But I'm still curious about a lot, so I'm putting my foot down!"


translate English day3_rs_5538139f:


    pl "What do you do every day to pass the time?"


translate English day3_rs_dec52adc:


    rs "Read."


translate English day3_rs_6e687827:


    pl "Picture books?"


translate English day3_rs_ff58abc1:


    rs "Yes, and?"


translate English day3_rs_e46afb68:


    pl "I wasn't trying to criticize you. If all you do is read books, when do you work?"


translate English day3_rs_d8f06d51:


    rs "Work? Do you mean assigned tasks, yes?"


translate English day3_rs_158f43cf:


    pl "Yeah. You must have work--you're a priest in the Academics Department."


translate English day3_rs_bf8b119f:


    nar "Then, for the second time, my words cut off for a moment."


translate English day3_rs_e5247206:


    pl "Wait wait wait! Do you not do any work? Or are you not actually part of the Academics Department at all?"


translate English day3_rs_e82faef8:


    rs "Rose works. And Rose is a priest of the Academics Department."


translate English day3_rs_fea41f96:


    pl "Then why not just say that?"


translate English day3_rs_09a3c0d9:


    rs "Because while that is true, it also... isn't."


translate English day3_rs_f4c20246:


    nar "Her words have been getting shorter and shorter. Can she not focus on the conversation?"


translate English day3_rs_85c9b434:


    pl "Oh... Well, I don't mean to barge in and ask all the questions. You said you were reading a book, right? Sorry for bothering you."


translate English day3_rs_fe58dff3:


    rs "A proper apology must be expressed with properly suitable actions."


translate English day3_rs_115c561f:


    pl "Ugh... I shouldn't have said that."


translate English day3_rs_2accfa8e:


    rs "If you are willing to express your apology with actions, then take the book farthest to the right on the fourth shelf down and read it, ordered Rose."


translate English day3_rs_e7d52f65:


    pl "Huh? Read it? Like, aloud?"


translate English day3_rs_70c9d772:


    rs "Yes."


translate English day3_rs_fc61bb09:


    pl "Ack. That's embarrassing..."


translate English day3_rs_2cf43df3:


    rs "Do you feel embarrassment from reading stories?"


translate English day3_rs_f177894b:


    pl "It's not that, it's just... Whatever. This is dumb. Fine, I'll just read it."


translate English day3_rs_3dcfeed2:


    nar "I go back to the bookshelf, then notice something."


translate English day3_rs_08f87734:


    nar "Most of the books on the shelves are thick dictionaries and technical books, but the fourth shelf down has children's stories and picture books on it."


translate English day3_rs_c448bc8f:


    nar "Maybe she needs to air out her brain with children's stories after reading all these wicked hard books or something."


translate English day3_rs_03976b52:


    nar "I can't really wrap my head around the idea of reading books to rest your brain."


translate English day3_rs_62e44edf:


    nar "I pick up the book and show it to Rose. She nods twice."


translate English day3_rs_472fb5ce:


    nar "The front cover has an illustration of a wave pattern that looks like it's supposed to represent the ocean. On the side, on the lower half of the cover, is a princess who is a mermaid from the waist down. I've never seen this book before."


translate English day3_rs_5d9b9e5e:


    pl "Errr. 'The distant ocean was beautiful, a blue much like...a...' Uh..."


translate English day3_rs_7cb9d3d3:


    nar "This embarrasses me to admit, but I get stuck on the first sentence."


translate English day3_rs_ce7e8de9:


    nar "I thought children's books were supposed to be easy for kids to read. Does this mean my literacy level is lower than that of children in the capital?"


translate English day3_rs_72d517e7:


    nar "I tried to skip over the word I couldn't read, but Rose breaks her watchful silence and opens her mouth right away."


translate English day3_rs_30c42634:


    rs "'A blue much like a cerulean chrysanthemum.'"


translate English day3_rs_a95c1d26:


    pl "Wait, if you already know this, then you don't need to make someone else read it for you."


translate English day3_rs_42146c11:


    rs "Rose wanted to hear it, and Rose requested as much. Do you not understand the language which she speaks?"


translate English day3_rs_388caed6:


    pl "...Actually, I'm a foreigner, so I still don't quite have a grip on how people talk here in the capital."


translate English day3_rs_963f7332:


    rs "Hmm... Rose also has difficulty with words."


translate English day3_rs_0cd71748:


    pl "Huh, really?"


translate English day3_rs_229af2b9:


    rs "Rose can easily read the words themselves, but they don't turn into information in her head."


translate English day3_rs_dfbfc214:


    rs "Hence, Rose is still unfamiliar with language."


translate English day3_rs_c30ece4f:


    pl "...If you're trying to comfort me, you really don't need to."


translate English day3_rs_07a9f5e1:


    rs "Incomprehensible."


translate English day3_rs_67e39faf:


    pl "It's not much different than what we spoke back home. I figure if I study a little, I'll learn to understand it, but..."


translate English day3_rs_67b1acd9:


    rs "Then study, answered Rose."


translate English day3_rs_6892626f:


    pl "You're gonna let me use this room so I can?"


translate English day3_rs_b56d8ad4:


    rs "Incomprehensible. Incomprehensible."


translate English day3_rs_7e1b05f7:


    pl "I mean, that's basically what you were implying, wasn't it?"


translate English day3_rs_2448505e:


    rs "Rose must not let outsiders into this space. [na] of the Cleanup Department, you are an outsider. "


translate English day3_rs_5a3db4de:


    rs "You are not permitted to enter. Get out."


translate English day3_rs_f6569e6f:


    pl "So cold... Fine, fine. I was just about to leave anyway."


translate English day3_rs_b883b4ff:


    rs "Bye-bye."


translate English day3_rs_ccb48d10:


    pl "But you're still saying bye to me... Well, bye."


translate English day3_rs_f07662bb:


    nar "Rose waves to me like she did before, then immediately flops back onto the blanket without watching to see if I actually leave. "


translate English day3_rs_75d685aa:


    nar "She's like a toy someone loosened the screws of."


translate English day3_rs_6960365b:


    nar "Is she actually human? Maybe if I come to the library again tomorrow, I'll figure something out."
